01 Oct 2019 05:05






I like the concept of bureaucratohazards and get a kick out of anomalous law, but nothing surrounding those concepts is fresh enough to enjoy. The core of the article reminds me of SCP-2557. The repetition of an anomalously inserted slogan like“perfectly legal, thank you very much” has been done so often I can’t list them all, but SCP-2602 especially comes to mind. The anomalous store itself reminds me of most everything dado, especially SCP-4525 — which I already didn’t like. Worst of all, the article isn’t really that funny. It replaces the gut-punch black comedy of SCP-1459 with a weak assortment of only mildly darkly humorous elements, to its own detriment.





